Place your GitHub SSH deploy key in this directory as a file named:

  GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY

The filename must match exactly — JCasC resolves ${GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY}
by looking for a file with that name in the secrets directory.

Example:
  cp ~/.ssh/my_deploy_key ./secrets/GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY
  chmod 600 ./secrets/GITHUB_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY

The key should be a standard PEM-format SSH private key:
  -----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
  ...
  -----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----

IMPORTANT: Never commit private keys to git.
